1.title: Claire Lynch
1.plot: Bad writing in wrestling is as inevitable as death and taxes - find out what happens when the best in Impact Wrestling have to deal with a pregnant crack addict named Claire Lynch.

2.title: Top 8 One-Time United States Champions
2.plot: Dozens of men have held the NWA/WCW/WWE United States Championship - fewer have only held it once - but only 8 of them belong on this list.

3.title: Hornswoggle, Vince McMahon's Son
3.plot: Think that Impact Wrestling has the market cornered on stupid storylines revolving around paternity and illegitimate children? Think again.

4.title: Firepower & Shutterspeed
4.plot: It's a DOUBLE FEATURE. This week, Brian reviews "Firepower" and "Shutterspeed", a pair of movies starring the Ultimate Warrior and Sting - which of these Blade Runners does a better job on the silver screen?

5.title: Top 8 Kurt Angle Wrestlemania Matches
5.plot: This year, WWE Hall of Famer Kurt Angle took part in his EIGHTH Wrestlemania. So what better way to celebrate than with a countdown that ranks all of his Mania matches.

6.title: Better Champion: JBL vs. Jinder Mahal
6.plot: It's been one year since Jinder Mahal shocked the world and became WWE Champion - so how did the Modern Day Maharajah's reign compare to that of JBL's, the LAST guy who shocked the world in 2004? Brian Zane takes a closer look.

7.title: Thunder in Paradise
7.plot: Baywatch meets Knight Rider meets HULKAMANIA, brother. It's time to look at the beginning of Hulk Hogan's short-lived TV series, THUNDER IN PARADISE.

8.title: by Real1 (Enzo Amore)
8.plot: Enzo Amore may officially be off the hook, but his new rap single "Phoenix", is not.

9.title: Top 16 Awesomely Bad Promos Part 1
9.plot: There are bad wrestling promos - then there are AWESOMELY bad wrestling promos. This week, Brian Zane counts down the best of the bad, from 16-9.

10.title: Top 16 Awesomely Bad Promos Part 2
10.plot: It's time to take a look at Brian Zane's top picks for the most awesomely bad wrestling promos of all-time.

11.title: Titus O'Neil, Unluckiest Man in WWE
11.plot: Has anyone in wrestling had more dumb stuff happen to them than the Gator? From the Keg Fail to the Greatest Royal Rumble, relive Titus O'Neil's greatest mishaps in WWE.

12.title: Boone: The Bounty Hunter
12.plot: America, it's time to get BOONE'd. Brian takes a look at John Morrison's passion project, "Boone: The Bounty Hunter".

13.title: Woman's Extreme Wrestling
13.plot: What happens when you want to honor the legacy of ECW, but only the part that's aged the worst? You get Women's Extreme Wrestling. Warning: This stuff is terrible.

14.title: WCW Invades Baywatch
14.plot: Hulk Hogan gets knocked out by a jetski, Randy Savage is always in gimmick, and Ric Flair wants to build condos?. It's what happens when WCW invades a "very special episode" of Baywatch.

15.title: A History of Wrestling's "Phantom Champions"
15.plot: Wrestling championships have changed hands hundreds of times throughout history - but not all of them have counted. Brian gives you a brief history of pro wrestling's "phantom champions".

16.title: Wrestling in Cartoons
16.plot: From Porky Pig to Kim Possible, wrestling has been featured in one way or another in animation for DECADES. A brief look back at some of the more memorable moments of wrestling and wrestler cameos in animated form.

17.title: Mucha Lucha
17.plot: Honor - family - tradition - DONUTS. To the characters in Mucha Lucha, masked wrestling is a way of life. Check out Brian's review of this early-2000's cartoon.

18.title: Mongo Wrestling Alliance
18.plot: From the man behind Metalocalypse, comes an absurd show that looks at a group of large, emotionally arrested wrestlers who leave chaos in the wake, to hilarious results. Brian takes a look at Mongo Wrestling Alliance.

19.title: WWE Slam City
19.plot: WWE and stop-motion animation - a match made in advertisement heaven??? Check out Brian's review of the long-form toy commercial that is, WWE Slam City.

20.title: Tiger Mask W
20.plot: It's the anime hit that'll make you fall in love with puroresu all over again. Brian reviews the New Japan vehicle that is, Tiger Mask W.

21.title: Top 8 Greatest Comebacks
21.plot: From in-ring injuries to medical conditions and more, here's a list of some of the greatest comebacks from some of the best wrestlers in history.

22.title: Marc Mero in the WWF
22.plot: First he was a Badd Man - then he was a Wildman - then he became MARVELOUS. Brian Zane takes a closer look at Marc Mero's career in the WWF, and how he may have actually been one of the most influential talents of the late 1990's.

23.title: Internet Darlings 2: UK Boogaloo
23.plot: Watch as Brian, Luke, Oli, Adam and Maffew gab about their experiences as YouTubers, the ups - and the downs.

24.title: A History of Royal Gimmicks
24.plot: This week, I take a look back at some of the more famous (and infamous) examples of royalty in professional wrestling, alongside a man who knows a thing or two about royalty - Ross Tweddell from Cultaholic.

25.title: Sports Gimmicks in Wrestling
25.plot: From the diamond to the gridion to the putting green and everywhere in-between, Brian Zane looks at some of the biggest examples of sports-related characters in wrestling's history.

26.title: Top 16 Smackdown Moments Part 1
26.plot: As we get closer to Smackdown 1000, it's time to rank the moments and matches that have helped define the Blue Brand's identity. Stay tuned to see what made the Top 8.

27.title: Top 16 Smackdown Moments Part 2
27.plot: You've seen the rest - now find out which moments from Smackdown's previous 1000 episodes have been the BEST.

28.title: The Dungeon of Doom
28.plot: In the mid-1990's, Kevin Sullivan was tasked with creating a force designed to get Hulk Hogan cheered by the WCW fans. He wasn't successful, but he sure seemed to have fun trying. Brian Zane takes a look at the ill-fated Dungeon of Doom.

29.title: The Masked Saint
29.plot: A wrestler-turned-pastor-turned-wrestler-again has to save his church AND his soul. Witness the film that features Roddy Piper in his final film role.

30.title: Should WWE Bring Back Intergender Wrestling?
30.plot: It's a debate that's been raging for years - should intergender wrestling return to WWE? Brian Zane breaks down why men wrestling women shouldn't be controversial.

31.title: The Lunchtime Suicides
31.plot: What happens when a depressed referee and an oblivious interviewer get together? More than three months of WWE's lame attempt at "comedy". Strap yourselves in for this one, folks.

32.title: XWF
32.plot: No More Prima Donnas. In Your Face. Same Old Crap. It's time to take a closer look at the short-lived dumpster fire of a federation known as, the XWF.

33.title: Eight MORE Gender Defying Reigns
33.plot: When one countdown isn't enough, Brian Zane dips into the well one more time to bring you some of the biggest examples of women winning men's championships, and vice-versa.

34.title: Wrestling's Best Ripoffs
34.plot: A quick history of some of the most successful copycats in professional wrestling. Proof that nothing in the wrestling is original.

35.title: Santa's Little Helper
35.plot: Deck the halls with another holiday romp starring The Miz - oh, and Paige is there too. It's time to take a look at the 2015 classic, Santa's Little Helper.

36.title: The Worst of WWE 2018
36.plot: It's time to look back at some of the worst there was in WWE in 2018.

37.title: The Best of WWE 2018
37.plot: It's time to look back at some of the best there was in WWE in 2018.

38.title: Hulk Hogan's Celebrity Championship Wrestling
38.plot: Hogan Knows Best might have been cancelled, but the Hulkster's reality TV career was still going strong in 2008 with Hulk Hogan's Celebrity Championship Wrestling. Dustin Diamond. Dennis Rodman. Danny Bonaduce. BROTHER DUDE JACK.

39.title: Top 8 Most Obscure Royal Rumble Entrants
39.plot: The Royal Rumble has played host to some of the biggest names in professional wrestling history - and also, these guys. Brian Zane takes a look at some of the most random and obscure entrants in Royal Rumble history.

40.title: The Chaperone
40.plot: This week, a special friend drops by to help Brian Zane review Triple H's magnum opus, THE CHAPERONE.

41.title: Rob Van Dam's Extreme Championship Comedy
41.plot: Rob Van Dam does stand-up comedy for a TV pilot, and it somehow manages to be both boring AND bad. Quite possibly the worst thing we have ever seen on this channel, feast your eyes on EXTREME CHAMPIONSHIP COMEDY.

1.title: Muhammad Hassan
1.plot: In the very first episode of Wrestling With Wregret, Brian Zane takes a look at how WWE had a golden opportunity with Muhammad Hassan - and how they screwed it all up.

2.title: NWF Kids Pro Wrestling
2.plot: Ah, the 1980's were a much simpler time. Brian Zane takes a look at the cable access sensation that was NWF Kids Pro Wrestling.

3.title: Strangest Repackagings
3.plot: From Akeem to Fake Diesel to Pirate Paul Burchill, Brian Zane looks back at some of the strangest and worst repackagings in wrestling history.

4.title: Worst Religious Gimmicks & Angles
4.plot: From preachers to zealots to battles with God, they're the gimmicks and angles that make you say, "Jesus Christ". Brian Zane takes a look at why religion and wrestling just don't mix.

5.title: Ready to Rumble
5.plot: A movie that actually made wrestling fans look WORSE, and the film that brought one of the most baffling PR stunts to pro wrestling. Brian Zane reviews "Ready to Rumble".

6.title: Abraxas
6.plot: Jesse Ventura was a loud, brash and larger-than-life character in professional wrestling - so why was it so hard to find a vehicle for him to express that character? Brian Zane examines Ventura's Terminator rip-off known as "Abraxas".

7.title: The Wrestling Albums & Piledriver
7.plot: The 1980's were a simpler time, when wrestlers could record an album or two and nobody would bat an eye. These have not aged well.

8.title: WWE Originals
8.plot: It's the 1980's all over again as Brian Zane reviews WWE Originals, the latest (and hopefully last) attempt at getting wrestlers to sing,

9.title: Knock-Off Wrestling Albums
9.plot: Who remembers seeing this deception at your local record store in the late 90's? Brian Zane and J Biggs listen to some of the worst tracks on these unauthorized wrestling theme albums.

10.title: Kayfabe in the 21st Century
10.plot: Where does kayfabe stand in today's world? Is there any point in keeping up the charade?

11.title: Darren Young Comes Out
11.plot: Darren Young becomes the first openly-gay wrestler to perform for WWE. Hear what Brian Zane has to say about the big news, and what should (and shouldn't!) happen in the aftermath.

12.title: Top 8 Worst Vince McMahon Storylines
12.plot: Check out Brian Zane's very first Top 8 countdown from 2013, in which he reviews the worst Vince McMahon Storylines.

13.title: Tazz in WWE
13.plot: Tazz was an unstoppable monster in ECW - but got swallowed whole in the land of the giants in the WWF. We take a look back at the WWF career of the Human Suplex Machine, and find out how it all went wrong.

14.title: Goldberg in WWE
14.plot: Witness the meteoric rise and fall of Bill Goldberg the FIRST time he was in WWE, when we all thought he would never come back and main-event at least two pay-per-views more than a decade later.

1.title: Shawn Crossen Interview
1.plot: The founder of the cable access sensation "NWF Kids Pro Wrestling" tells his side of the story in this special interview.

2.title: DX, 2006-Style!
2.plot: Brian Zane takes a look at DX, from their time in 2006.

3.title: nWWEo
3.plot: Brian Zane takes a trip down memory lane and talks about the WWE version of the NWO.

4.title: WWECW!
4.plot: Brian Zane takes a closer look at the debacle that was WWE's revival of ECW as a third brand. The zombies. The stripping. The Lashley.

5.title: The F*&%Ing Invasion
5.plot: Reboot Month concludes with a "fond" look back at the storyline that killed the passion for many a wrestling fan - the WCW/ECW Invasion storyline.

6.title: Pie
6.plot: Check out Brian Zane's take on The Rock's solo music debut, the godawful song "Pie" featuring Slick Rick.

7.title: The Great Benoit Debate
7.plot: The debate has raged for years now...what is the appropriate way for WWE to present Chris Benoit? Is it truly possible for fans to separate the wrestler from the murderer? Brian Zane takes a closer look.

8.title: Crappy NES Wrestling Games
8.plot: Brian Zane and R Felix Finch make their way through some of the most memorable wrestling games on the original NES console...let's see how these games have aged over the years.

9.title: Crappy N64 Wrestling Games
9.plot: Brian Zane and R Felix Finch slog their way through some of the worst wrestling games on the Nintendo 64.

10.title: The Daniel Debacle
10.plot: Where do you stand in the Daniel Bryan debate?

11.title: Wrestlers in Commercials
11.plot: Who else got excited to see their favorite wrestlers appearing in commercials as a kid? The luster sure wears off as an adult, though...Brian Zane looks at some of the strangest wrestling-based commercials seen on TV.

12.title: Top 8 Worst Kane Storylines
12.plot: After nearly 20 years in WWE, you can bet that Kane has been involved in some pretty dumb storylines, in this video, Brian Zane counts down the 8 worst of all-time, besides Katie Vick.

13.title: Exposed! Pro Wrestling's Greatest Secrets
13.plot: Back when wrestling got big, everyone wanted a piece of the action. Brian Zane looks back at the infamous TV special that pulled back the veil and revealed the "big secrets" of professional wrestling.

14.title: My First Match
14.plot: From deep within the Z-Vault...never-before-seen footage of my very first match back in 2004 in Portland, OR. Yes, I am aware that it is horrible.

15.title: Too Many Champions
15.plot: Do you think belt=star? Do you think your favorite wrestler winning the title will help the WWE enter a boom period? What do you think about a title's lineage when too many people win it?

16.title: Wrestling Society X
16.plot: It was the wildest, most frenetic ADD-friendly half-hour on basic cable - but was it actually wrestling? Brian Zane looks at the one and only season of Wrestling Society X.

17.title: Michael Modest Interview
17.plot: Brian Zane does a phone interview with former WWE and WCW wrestler about his time on Exposed. Pro Wrestling's Greatest Secrets.

18.title: Top 8 Worst Wrestlemanias
18.plot: 31 Wrestlemanias have come and gone (well, 30 at the time this review came out) - and while some have been revered as some of the all-time great cards, some of them have sucked. Very hard. Brian Zane looks at some of the worst.

1.title: The Wrestler
1.plot: "The Wrestler" is one of the worst movies about wrestling in history, no, not the movie starring Mickey Rourke, the one from 70's starring Verne Gagne. Witness the horror of what might as well have been called the Verne Gagne biopic.

2.title: No More #Hijacking
2.plot: Sometimes, wrestling crowds LOVE to hijack shows and let 'em know how they feel. What do you think when crowds take over? Let me know in the comments section below.

3.title: Panic for TNA?
3.plot: With Spike TV not renewing TNA's contract, is this the end for TNA?

4.title: Game Show Mania!
4.plot: Pro wrestling and game shows are two things that seem to exist in their own little universes. So what happens when these worlds collide? What happens when pro wrestlers invade game shows? Robert Seidelman helps Brian Zane find the answer.

5.title: Rich Face, Smart Face?
5.plot: Picture this: A wrestler whose gimmick revolves primarily around their fabulous wealth or their supreme intelligence - being portrayed as a good guy. CAN IT BE DONE?

6.title: Top 8 Worst Thongs About the Attitude Era
6.plot: The WWF's Attitude Era was great and all, but it wasn't without its share of embarrassing and stupid stuff. Zane counts down the worst of it.

7.title: WWF Raw & WWE Wrestlemania 21
7.plot: In a continuation of WWW's look into crappy wrestling games, Brian Zane and R Felix Finch play two WWE titles for the Xbox: Raw and Wrestlemania 21. And introducing one of the DEADLIEST WEAPONS in a wrestling game.

8.title: Backyard Wrestling 1 & 2
8.plot: What's worse than wrestling in your backyard? Wrestling in your backyard - IN A VIDEO GAME. Brian Zane an R Felix Finch play the Backyard Wrestling games on the Xbox.

9.title: The Simpsons Wrestling
9.plot: Don't have a cow, man, but this is truly one of the worst wrestling games of all-time. Brian Zane and R Felix Finch play the PS1 dumpster fire known as Simpsons Wrestling.

10.title: Joe Rogan & MMA Fans
10.plot: Joe Rogan took a jab at pro wrestling and its fans on a recent episode of his podcast - and Brian Zane isn't going to take that lying down.

11.title: The One and Only
11.plot: The Fonz and wrestling - what could go wrong? Brian Zane takes a look at the 70's Carl Reiner flick "The One And Only" starring Henry Winkler.

12.title: CM Punk Breaks His Silence
12.plot: Brian Zane talks about CM Punk on the Art of Wrestling podcast.

13.title: The Worst Action Figures
13.plot: Every wrestling fan who started out as a kid has memories of throwing down with their friends in a battle for action figure supremacy - but Brian Zane highlights some Toys R Us rejects that deserve to be melted down.

14.title: Body Slam
14.plot: What happens when the guy from The A-Team teams up with Roddy Piper and the Tonga Kid in one of the worst wrestling films of all-time? You get "Body Slam", of course.

15.title: Trash Bag Wrestlers
15.plot: Brian Zane is sick this week - And it's all because of an increase in TRASH BAG WRESTLERS.

16.title: My Top 8 Favorite Wrestlers
16.plot: Brian Zane breaks the chain of negativity by revealing the eight wrestlers who make him smile.

17.title: New Year's Wresolutions
17.plot: What are YOUR wrestling hopes and dreams in the year 2015?

18.title: The Reign of Terror
18.plot: It was the three-year span that flat-out KILLED the passion for some wrestling fans - Triple H's "Reign of Terror" on WWE Raw. Brian Zane takes a look back.

1.title: Grand Masters of Wrestling Part 1
1.plot: What happens when a bunch of past-their-prime legends congregate under one tent in a cul-de-sac? You get one of the worst sets of DVDs of all-time, Grand Masters of Wrestling.

2.title: Grand Masters of Wrestling Part 2
2.plot: What could be worse than the first two Grand Masters of Wrestling DVDs? How about the NEXT TWO Grand Masters of Wrestling DVDs. It's everything you loved about the first MaccabiahMania show, except everyone is four years older now.

3.title: Top 8 Worst Wrestling Themes
3.plot: They're the tunes that make you groan and cry out in pain. What are your least favorite theme songs in wrestling?

4.title: WWE Network, One Year Later
4.plot: It's been one year this week since the WWE Network went live in the United States.

5.title: DDP in WWE
5.plot: Diamond Dallas Page was one of WCW's biggest stars - but when he moved to the WWF? Eh, not so much. Brian Zane breaks down the problems with his WWF run.

6.title: The "Legend" of Supertramp
6.plot: Does the pro wrestler "Super Tramp" exist? Yes, but only in the sad, sad mind of the man who created him. Brian Zane exposes this BFF and tells you how to spot one in your area.

7.title: Wrestling Madness Board Game
7.plot: Can the nuances of professional wrestling transfer over to the board game world? Brian Zane finds out when he plays this obscure number with a confusing history, Wrestling Madness.

8.title: Be a Man
8.plot: What better way to honor the Macho Man's induction into the WWE Hall of Fame, than to look at his amazingly awful 2003 rap album?

9.title: WWE Wrestlemania 31 Review
9.plot: Wrestlemania 31 is in the books. A wild ladder match, the Triple-Nator, Sting as Doc Brown, Suplex City and more.

10.title: The DeMott DeBate
10.plot: Where do you stand on the Bill DeMott controversy? Were his alleged training methods just tough love - or did it go too far?

11.title: Should Wrestlers Unionize?
11.plot: It's the age-old question: Should wrestlers be able to form a labor union? It's not just promoters who are against the idea.

12.title: Brand Split Retrospective
12.plot: The WWE Brand Split and all that it gave us divided not only rosters, but wrestling fans as well. Where do you stand on the 13-year-long experiment?

13.title: WrestleCrate Unboxing
13.plot: Brain Zane does in unboxing of the first ever WrestleCrate.

15.title: Sting: Moment of Truth
15.plot: What happens when one of the biggest names in all of wrestling makes a low-budget movie about his journey to Christianity, chock-full of montages and historical inaccuracies?

17.title: The Problem with NXT
17.plot: Has NXT become too good for its own good?

18.title: Ultimate WrestleCrate Unboxing
18.plot: Brian Zane does an unboxing of the Ultimate WrestleCrate.

19.title: All the Marbles
19.plot: Did you know that Peter Falk once starred in a 1981 movie about women's wrestling? Did you know that it was also boring as all get-out? Brian Zane takes a look at the film "All The Marbles". Featuring TELEPORTATION.

20.title: Top 8 Worst Heel Turns
20.plot: There are heel turns that needed work - and some heel turns that flat-out DIDN'T work. Brian Zane takes a look at some of the worst heel turns in wrestling history.

21.title: Hulk Hogan Scandal
21.plot: Hulk Hogan FIRED from WWE after a transcript of his racist comments are released. While he hasn't been "erased" from history like some people are quick to say, he is certainly being downplayed.

1.title: Eddie Guerrero
1.plot: Has Brian Zane's spirit finally been broken? What kind of madness has been laid before him? Find out, as Brian takes a look back at WWE's exploitation of the death of Eddie Guerrero.

2.title: The Jesse Ventura Story
2.plot: What do Kanyon, Goldberg and Raven have to do with Jesse Ventura? Not a damn thing, but that didn't stop NBC from shoving them into this poorly-made network TV biopic that "The Body" wanted nothing to do with.

3.title: Top 8 Worst Finishers
3.plot: Counting down the least realistic, least interesting, and least effective finishing moves in wrestling history.

4.title: More Bad Commercials
4.plot: Happy Thanksgiving from Wrestling With Wregret. As you work to digest all that food you ate, sit back and enjoy some more laughably bad commercials with wrestlers in them.

5.title: You Can't See Me
5.plot: Remember when people used to LIKE John Cena? Things took a turn for the worse once this album came out. Brian Zane listens to the one and only album by the Doctor of Thuganomics and his sidekick Tha Trademarc.

6.title: WWE Offseason?!
6.plot: Is it possible? Has Brian Zane found an offseason formula that would benefit wrestlers, fans, AND WWE?

7.title: Worse Champ: Jericho or Mysterio?
7.plot: Rey Mysterio and Chris Jericho, which man goes down as having the worst championship reign in history? Zane compares Rey's time as WHC in 2006 and Y2J's run as Undisputed Champion in 2001 to see which one is truly the lowest of the low.

8.title: Woman of Wrestling Unleashed
8.plot: Before there was Wrestlicious...but after there was GLOW...there was WOW. Let's watch their cringe-tastic 2001 PPV together.

9.title: Top 8 Worst of WWE in 2015
9.plot: It's been a wild year for WWE, and with 2015 wrapping up, Brian Zane gives his take on the top 8 WORST things to happen in the company during the last calendar year.

10.title: Top 8 Best of WWE in 2015
10.plot: We like to poke fun at WWE, but we would be remiss if we didn't mention some of the actual GOOD stuff they did this year. Brian Zane counts down the top 8 BEST things WWE did in 2015.

11.title: Rodman Down Under
11.plot: Brian Zane starts the year off by reviewing one of the most cringeworthy PPV events of all-time...but he's not going it alone. Witness as BZ and Phelous take apart "Rodman Down Under".

12.title: Top 8 Worst Dancing Wrestlers
12.plot: Dancing wrestlers have been a part of the landscape since almost forever, but for every Rikishi and Ernest Miller, there are scores of other, much worse dancing wrestlers. This week, Brian Zane counts down the worst of them all.

13.title: Worst Second & Third Generation Wrestlers
13.plot: Some second and third generation wrestlers are simply destined for greatness but for every Bret Hart or Randy Orton, there are tons of other men and women who just don't cut it.

14.title: Kevin Kleinrock Interview Part 1
14.plot: The creator of MTV's Wrestling Society X stops by to give us HIS side of the story.

15.title: Kevin Kleinrock Interview Part 2
15.plot: In Part Two, the creator of Wrestling Society X talks about the most controversial moment in the show's history, what led to WSX's cancellation, comparisons to Lucha Underground and more.

16.title: Top 8 Worst Gimmick Matches
16.plot: Hell In A Cell...the Ladder Match...War Games...these are just some of the matches that WON'T be on this list. Brian Zane looks at some of the dumbest gimmick matches of all-time.

17.title: Top 8 Worst Debuts
17.plot: You only get one chance to make a first impression - and these guys didn't make a good one. Ranking some of the worst debuts in wrestling.

18.title: Wrestling Food Taste Test
18.plot: Brian Zane and J Biggs join forces to consume decades-old wrestling food items. Sorry, no ice cream bars here.

19.title: Heroes of Wrestling
19.plot: It's the video you've all been asking for. Wrestling With Wregret tackles one of the most infamous PPVs of all-time, Heroes of Wrestling. Brian is joined by none other than Adam From WhatCulture and they meet a surprise guest?

20.title: Top 8 Worst Things About the Wrestlemania Rage Party
20.plot: Remember back before Axxess was a thing? Fans today don't know how good they have it. Brian Zane looks back at the Wrestlemania Rage Party from 1999.

21.title: Top 8 Best Wrestlemanias
21.plot: Will Wrestlemania 32 join this esteemed list? Probably not. But that doesn't mean you shouldn't relax and enjoy this look back at the best Wrestlemanias of all-time, as voted on by YOU, the fans.

22.title: 100,000 Subscribers - Q & A
22.plot: As promised, I answer some of your burning questions as we celebrate the channel reaching 100,000 subscribers.

23.title: Million Dollar Tough Enough
23.plot: It's the season of Tough Enough not good enough to get its own cable timeslot...the season that killed the franchise for years...and yet somehow produced the most WWE talent?

24.title: Donald Trump in WWE
24.plot: When Donald Trump isn't running his business or being president, he's responsible for some of the WORST storylines in WWE history. Brian Zane explains why.

25.title: Why We'll Never See Another Monday Night War
25.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

26.title: See No Evil
26.plot: MAY 19TH . - MAY 19TH - MAY 19TH. It's the tenth anniversary of the release of WWE Films' first movie, "See No Evil" starring Kane. And slasher expert The Horror Guru is helping Brian Zane out with this one.

27.title: Why New Japan Can't Compete with WWE
27.plot: Don't get me wrong, New Japan Pro Wrestling is awesome - but I'm just not sure they can compete for WWE's market share in America.

28.title: No Holds Barred
28.plot: Brian Zane Reviews "No Holds Barred" starring Hulk Hogan.

1.title: Brawl for All
1.plot: Brian Zane tackles what was the stupidest thing to happen to WWF, The Brawl for All.

2.title: Wrestlicious
2.plot: Wrestlicious, the all-female league that was somehow WORSE than Women of Wrestling. It's the 80's kitsch of GLOW, yet it happened in 2010 - what were they thinking?

3.title: Top 8 Favorite WWE Themes
3.plot: Brian Zane counts down his top 8 favorite WWE themes.

4.title: Why Are Fans So Skeptical?
4.plot: Brian Zane reveals his three least favorite words by some of today's fans, attempts to explore what has caused them to become so jaded and cynical, and why it's not their fault.

5.title: Bret Hart in WCW
5.plot: Bret Hart was one of the best wrestlers alive, heading to WCW after an illustrious run with the WWF - so why did it all go wrong for the Hitman? Brian Zane investigates.

6.title: Los Luchadores
6.plot: Los Luchadores was a short-lived live-action series from the early 2000's. Sure, it's for kids - but that doesn't mean Brian Zane isn't going to skewer the crap out of it.

7.title: Top 8 Worst "New" Thing in Wrestling
7.plot: In wrestling, new things can be good: New wrestlers, new storylines, that sort of thing. But just putting the word "New" in front of something does NOT count. Brian Zane looks at the worst of it all.

9.title: Pro Wrestling vs. Zombies
9.plot: As you get ready for Halloween weekend, enjoy the infamous zombie film that's so bad, it's scary. Featuring Roddy Piper, Shane Douglas, Jim Duggan and Kurt Angle.

10.title: Top 8 Worst Scary Wrestlers
10.plot: Brian Zane counts down his Top 8 Worst Scary Wrestlers.

11.title: Eugene
11.plot: Eugene was one of the most memorable and polarizing characters in WWE history - but was he as bad and offensive as some people make it out to be? And can Brian withstand the wrath of the Know-It-All Fan.

12.title: Top 8 "What Ifs" of the Attitude Era
12.plot: Pro wrestling is full of "what-ifs" - and there are enough of those in the WWE's Attitude Era that could have changed the entire landscape of professional wrestling. Brian Zane counts down some of the biggest of them all.

13.title: The WCW Mini Movies
13.plot: Spin The Wheel, Make the Deal. White Castle of Fear. Beach Blast 93. Brian Zane looks back at the infamous trilogy of WCW Mini Movies from the early 1990's that were full of unintentional comedy.

14.title: Forgotten Ruthless Aggression Wrestlers Part 1
14.plot: This Thanksgiving week, enjoy a smorgasbord of forgettable grapplers with an unprecedented TOP 24 COUNTDOWN of the Most Forgettable Ruthless Aggression-Era Wrestlers.

15.title: Forgotten Ruthless Aggression Wrestlers Part 2
15.plot: It's part 2 of the Most Forgettable Ruthless Aggression Era Wrestlers. So many bodies, so few memories. Truly, this WWE era was a confusing time.

16.title: Forgotten Ruthless Aggression Wrestlers Part 3
16.plot: Happy Thanksgiving, everybody. Before you gorge on a bunch of foodstuffs, enjoy this bounty of forgettable Ruthless Aggression-era wrestlers. The biggest names that made you go - huh?

17.title: Ultimate Warrior in WCW
17.plot: SPEAK TO ME, WARRIORS. Brian Zane takes a look back at the Ultimate Warrior's tumultuous run in WCW, including his dumpster fire of a match with Hollywood Hogan at Halloween Havoc.

18.title: Wrestling's Best Talkers (70s-Mid 90s)
18.plot: This week, we count down the best promo guys in all of wrestling, as voted by you, the fans. This video takes a closer look at microphone masters from the 70s to the mid-90s.

19.title: Wrestling's Best Talkers (Mid 90s-Today)
19.plot: It's time to count down the greatest promo guys in wrestling over the last 20 years, as voted on by you, the fans.

20.title: Santa with Muscles
20.plot: Ho-Ho-Hogan. Brian Zane and Puppet take a closer look at what is considered one of the worst movies of all-time, "Santa With Muscles" starring Hulk Hogan. Featuring Clint Howard, Garrett Morris, and debilitating head trauma.

21.title: Santa's Slay
21.plot: Before Goldberg destroyed Brock Lesnar at this year's Survivor Series, he was killing people in Santa's Slay. Brian Zane and WhatCulture's Adam Blampied delve into this Yuletide gorefest.

22.title: The Worst of WWE 2016
22.plot: 2016 is almost over. As we get ready to toss this year into the dumpster and set it aflame, let's relive some of the worst of WWE in 2016.

23.title: The Best of WWE 2016
23.plot: 2016 got ya down? Buck up, buttercup. Brian Zane counts down his picks for the best things about WWE in 2016.

24.title: The Nexus
24.plot: Brian Zane takes a closer look at one of WWE's last great invasion angles that was ruined before its time. Witness in horror as the career trajectories of several promising young wrestlers are destroyed by Super Cena and plain old bad luck.

25.title: WWE Unauthorized
25.plot: Buckle up for a review of WWE Unauthorized, a slapdash retelling of the history of WWE that was made without any cooperation from the company. Find out why the word "Unauthorized" usually means, "full of crap"

26.title: Great Wrestlers, Bad Masks
26.plot: Masked wrestlers can be great, but sometimes, great wrestlers WEARING masks can suck. Brian Zane takes a look at some of the most infamous examples of great in-ring performers who had embarrassing masked gimmicks in wrestling.

27.title: The Grudge Match
27.plot: After Abraxas but before becoming Governor of Minnesota, Jesse Ventura took part in this ridiculous short-lived game show, The Grudge Match. It was a giant food fight where the winner was decided by the fans - what could go wrong?

28.title: The XFL
28.plot: As we approach the 16th anniversary of Vince McMahon's one-and-done football league, Brian Zane and the Know-It-All-Fan look back at the good and bad of one of the biggest failures in WWE history.

29.title: Wrestling Commercials Part 3
29.plot: It's the return of wrestling commercials. On this edition, we cover beer, more beer, laser tag, the baseball strike and more.

30.title: Just Another Romantic Wrestling Comedy
30.plot: Valentines Day has come and gone, so here's a rom-com jam-packed with terrible jokes about Jews and gay people, but not much actual wrestling. Oh, and Chyna is in this, too. Literally, the worst movie I've ever seen.

31.title: Top 8 Best Black Wrestlers
31.plot: This week, Brian celebrates some of the best black wrestlers in the history of the sport. From the multiple-time champions, to the territorial journeymen you may never have heard of.

32.title: World Wrestling All-Stars
32.plot: After the death of WCW but before the arrival of TNA, one company emerged as an alternative to the WWF - an alternative that looked awfully similar to both. This is the story of World Wrestling All-Stars, aka, WCW/TNA Lite.

33.title: Strategy Guide VHS
33.plot: This week, Brian Zane reviews a hidden gem of the WWE video library - the video strategy guide to Wrestlemania: The Arcade Game. Featuring Bret Hart with a necktie, and the Undertaker saying "DEMON DIZZY".

34.title: Top 8 Celebrities Who Belong in the WWE Hall of Fame
34.plot: People love to hate the Celebrity Wing of the WWE Hall of Fame - but what if they inducted celebrities who actually DESERVED it?

35.title: Top 8 Worst Wrestlemania Matches
35.plot: As we approach Wrestlemania 33, it's time to look back at some of the best - and the worst - of what the Showcase of the Immortals has to offer. This week, Brian Zane counts down the worst Wrestlemania matches of all-time.

36.title: Top 8 Best Wrestlemania Matches
36.plot: We're just days away from Wrestlemania 33, and it's time to reflect on the matches that have made the event great. Featuring Bret Hart, Shawn Michaels and a few others.

37.title: Scooby-Doo: Wrestlemania Mystery
37.plot: It's time for Animation Month on Wrestling With Wregret. We're kicking things off with a review of "Scooby-Doo: Wrestlemania Mystery".

38.title: The Flintstones & WWE: Stone Age Smackdown
38.plot: Wrestling With Wregret's Animation Month rolls on as we review "The Flintstones and WWE: Stone Age Smackdown". It's Yabba-Dabba-Deplorable.

39.title: Scooby-Doo & WWE: Curse of the Speed Demon
39.plot: In this installment of Animation Month, we go back to the world of Scooby-Doo with "Curse of the Speed Demon". How will this cinematic equivalent of Crush Hour stack up with the rest of this month's offering.

40.title: Hulk Hogan's Rock 'n' Wrestling
40.plot: Pour yourself big bowl of cereal and sit down in front of the TV set, because we're going back to Saturday mornings in the 1980's. Brian Zane reviews "Hulk Hogan's Rock 'n' Wrestling" series for Animation Month.

41.title: Surf's Up 2: WaveMania
41.plot: We're in the home stretch of Animation Month. This week, we take a closer look at Surf's Up 2: WaveMania, featuring Mr. McMahon milking a fish.

42.title: The Jetsons & WWE: Robo-Wrestlemania
42.plot: Brian Zane reviews The Jestsons and WWE: Robo-Wrestlemania.

1.title: Wanna Be the Strongest in the World
1.plot: It's the final installment of Animation Month (Plus One Week). Brian kicks off Season 7 of WWW with boobies, camels and crabs - it's the bizarre wrestling anime "Wanna Be The Strongest In the World".

2.title: Hulk Rules
2.plot: Remember when I said how bad it was that Hulk Hogan was nowhere to be seen on those old WWF albums? Boy, was I wrong. Time to listen to the ultimate vanity project, "Hulk Rules".

3.title: Backyard Dogs
3.plot: Remember when backyard wrestling was all the rage? Let this movie from 2000 serve as a reminder why it's not that great. Starring the original Black Power Ranger, the future Rosalee from "Grimm", and Jesse Hernandez.

4.title: Universal Wrestling Federation (Herb Abrams)
4.plot: It's a story of about wrestling, politics, drugs, and MULLETS. It's the story of Herb Abrams and the Universal Wrestling Federation. Thanks to the Patreon backers for helping me reach my first stretch goal.

5.title: 8 Outrageous LGBT Gimmicks (and 1 Subtle one)
5.plot: Gimmicks of a homosexual nature in pro wrestling are nothing new, but there are some over the last 25 years that have been TRULY outrageous. Brian Zane counts them down, with a special guest.

6.title: My Interview with LGBT Wrestlers
6.plot: Brian Zane interviews four independent wrestlers who fall under the LGBT umbrella. Hear their stories about their feelings getting into the business, their relationships with fans and colleagues, what they think about "flamboyant" gimmicks.

7.title: Top 8 Favorite Wregret Videos
7.plot: Four years ago this week, the Wrestling With Wregret channel was born. Now, Brian Zane takes a self-indulgent tour of some of his favorite reviews, sketches and music videos he's ever done. You're welcome.

8.title: The Diva Search
8.plot: How does WWE do "classy"? Find out as Brian looks back at one of the wildest competitions in the company's history, the Diva Search. Featuring Kamala, The Rock and pies.

9.title: When Racial Stereotypes Got Over
9.plot: Throughout wrestling history, there have been a LOT of characters based on crude ethnic and racial stereotypes. And while it makes sense for HEELS using such tactics to get booed, it's fascinating when BABYFACES get cheered with them.

10.title: The WCW Championship in 2000
10.plot: Witness the dumpster fire that was World Championship Wrestling in the year 2000. Multiple World Title vacancies. David Arquette and Vince Russo as champion. Ready to Rumble. Brian Zane traces the journey of the WCW Championship during the company's final full year in existence.

11.title: Worse Champion: Rollins or Owens?
11.plot: Seth Rollins as WWE Champion - Kevin Owens as Universal Champion - which guy had it worse? Brian Zane compares the two ill-fated championship reigns to try and find out which one should be considered the worse one.

12.title: Scott Steiner in WWE
12.plot: HOLLER IF YA HEAR ME. It's time to look back at Scott Steiner's singles run in WWE, from his disastrous feud with Triple H, to his debate on the merits of the Iraq War, to his on-again/off-again partnership with Test. BOOM SHAKA LAKA!!.

13.title: GLOW on GLOW Part 1
13.plot: Netflix debuted their GLOW series to much fanfare. In the first of this two-part interview series, see how GLOW originals Roxy Astor, Gremlina, MTV and Sunny the California Girl are responding to the series, and what it was missing.

14.title: GLOW on GLOW Part 2
14.plot: Brian Zane interviews GLOW originals Hollywood, Godiva and Little Egypt to get their thoughts on the GLOW Netflix series. How did they react to this fictionalized account of the promotion? How was the dynamic between David McLane and Matt Cimber similar to that of their Netflix counterparts? Plus, learn which actor one lady thinks should be up for an Emmy.

15.title: Nacho Libre
15.plot: Let's go back to 2006, when wrestling was awful and Jack Black was at his peak. It's time to review Nacho Libre.

16.title: Zach Gowen in WWE
16.plot: Zach Gowen is one of wrestling's most inspirational figures - but that didn't make his brief run in WWE any less painful to watch. Brian Zane takes a look at what went wrong with this one-legged grappler.

17.title: Top 8 Marty Jannettys
17.plot: It's not unusual to see tag teams break up - it IS unusual to see both guys do well for themselves afterward. I count down some of the biggest examples of the "Marty Jannetty" phenomenon in wrestling.

18.title: American Wrestling Federation
18.plot: This week, we take a look at a promotion that tries to make a new wheel, but using old parts. How the American Wrestling Federation tried to "bring wrestling back to its roots" in four-minute increments.

19.title: Wrestlers in Music Videos Part 1
19.plot: Brian Zane takes a look at just some of the wild music videos that have featured pro wrestlers. From the awesome, to the why-did-this-get-made.

20.title: Wrestlers in Music Videos Part 2
20.plot: Brian Zane is back with another set of music videos featuring wrestlers. Roddy Piper thinks he can sing, The Rock hangs out with Wyclef Jean, and the Big Show in a video for - THE THONG SONG.

21.title: Raven in WWE
21.plot: This week, Brian Zane looks at the era of Raven in WWE. From bad luck to bad booking to bad karma, find out how one of the most captivating characters of the 1990s got lost in the shuffle.

22.title: Learning The Ropes
22.plot: Go back to the 1980's, a simpler time with simpler sitcoms. Time to review "Learning The Ropes", starring Lyle Alzado and the stars of the National Wrestling Alliance.

23.title: Tag Team
23.plot: It's a special LIVE review at the Nerdist Showroom at Meltdown Comics in Los Angeles. Brian Zane, Steve and Larson and special guest Rob Fee review the 1991 TV pilot for "Tag Team" starring Roddy Piper and Jesse Ventura.

24.title: Wrestlers in Sitcoms
24.plot: It's an institution of television - the sitcom. In a *very special episode*, Brian Zane looks at the history of wrestlers in sitcoms through the decades.

25.title: The Rise & Fall of Zack Ryder
25.plot: Zack Ryder got the fans on his side with his hard work and creativity. Then cold, hard reality set in.

26.title: Monster Brawl
26.plot: It's that time of year, so settle in for a SPOOKY review of Monster Brawl, a film in which monsters - um, brawl.

27.title: The Marine
27.plot: All this November, Brian reviews the Marine movies produced by WWE Films. We're beginning with 2006's "The Marine", which is John Cena's first leading film role - and it shows.

28.title: The Marine 2
28.plot: We've seen what John Cena can do as The Marine - find out what happens when bland second-generation star Ted DiBiase Jr. takes on the starring role in The Marine 2.

29.title: The Marine 3: Homefront
29.plot: OOH-RAH, it's Marine Month. We look at the first movie in the franchise starring The Miz, The Marine 3: Homefront. Find out how the most must-see superstar in WWE stacks up to John Cena and Ted DiBiase.

30.title: The Marine 4: Moving Target
30.plot: We're heading into the home stretch of Marine Month. This week, Brian Zane looks at The Marine 4, starring The Miz and "starring" Summer Rae.

31.title: The Marine 5: Battleground
31.plot: It's here. Marine Month wraps up with a look at The Marine 5: Battleground. Full of running up and down a parking structure, a man slowly bleeding out, and the Social Outcasts as bikers.

32.title: Christmas Bounty
32.plot: Christmas season is upon us. Or should I say - MIZmas?!? It's time to watch Christmas Bounty, a made-for-TV family film that involves bounty hunters trying to take down the mob.

33.title: Top 8 Jewish Wrestlers
33.plot: Shalom. In honor of Hanukkah starting this week, we're going to look back and celebrate some of the best Jewish wrestlers of all-time, so grab your latkes and applesauce, and spin the dreidel until you plotz.

34.title: Top 8 Good Things About the Invasion
34.plot: The Invasion Storyline is widely known as one of the biggest blown opportunities in wrestling history - but it turns out, there was actually some good to come out of it. Brian Zane breaks down the silver linings of the Invasion.

35.title: The Worst of WWE 2017
35.plot: As this year comes to a close, it's time to look back at the good and the bad of WWE - today, Brian gives you the bad news first.

36.title: The Best of WWE 2017
36.plot: What will make Brian's best-of list for WWE in 2017? Find out in the final countdown of the year.

37.title: Sting in WWE
37.plot: The Icon - The Franchise - The Vigilante??? A look at Sting's brief, illogical, nonsensical run in WWE.

38.title: Wrestling Food Taste Test: The Return
38.plot: Brian Zane and J Biggs return with another bunch of outdated wrestling snacks to try. Popcorn, energy drinks, gummies and more stuff that probably wasn't even good when it was fresh.

39.title: Top 8 One-Time Intercontinental Champions
39.plot: The WWE Intercontinental Championship has a rich tradition and history, and has been held by some of the best wrestlers of all-time. Some have held it a lot, while dozens have held it only once. Brian Zane counts down his picks for the best one-timers of all-time.

40.title: WWF Aggression
40.plot: Brian Zane takes a look at WWF Aggression, a CD that came out in 2000.

41.title: Ring of Glory
41.plot: What happens when one of the most polarizing figures in wrestling history starts a brand-new organization dedicated to spreading the gospel of the Lord? I SWEAH TO GAWD - it's Vince Russo's "Ring of Glory".

42.title: Top 8 WWE Opponents for AJ Styles
42.plot: It's no secret that AJ Styles is a great wrestler. He's had some great matches since coming to WWE - but think of all the great matches he COULD have. Brian counts down his top dream opponents for the Phenomenal One.

43.title: The Insane Clown Posse
43.plot: WHOOP WHOOP. What happens when "the most hated band in music" gets involved in professional wrestling? Find out as Brian takes a look at the Insane Clown Posse in the WWF, WCW, TNA and even Ring of Honor.

44.title: Top 8 WWE Stars Who Did Better in TNA
44.plot: Impact Wrestling isn't just a place for older WWE stars to go out to pasture - it's also a place where untapped potential can finally be realized. Take a look at some of the biggest examples of WWE wrestlers who did BETTER in TNA/Impact.

45.title: Trying WCW Cologne, WWE Talking Soap & More
45.plot: It's the most bizarre "trial" video I've done yet. I scoured the internet to find wrestling-branded hygiene products to try out on-camera - From shampoo, to talking soap (?!) to WCW cologne, I hope to smell like a rose when this is all done.

46.title: A Pain in he Ads: Wrestling Commercials Part 4
46.plot: Commercials, bad. Wrestlers in commercials, good. Brian Zane takes yet another look at some classic commercials starring the stars of the squared circle.

47.title: Top 8 Favorite Championship Belt Designs
47.plot: Belts, belts everywhere. Brian Zane counts down his favorite championship designs through the years.

48.title: Wrestlemania the Album
48.plot: ARE YOU READY FOR THE SURVIVOR SERIES? Wait - that can't be right. Brian Zane takes a look at the Wrestlemania Album.

49.title: Kurt Angle's Most Outrages Heel Moments
49.plot: Going from good guy to bad guy is common in wrestling - but when Kurt Angle went heel, sometimes it went a little too far. This week, Brian and special guest Vee Infuso (the Social Injustice Warrior) take a closer look at the darkest days of Kurt's time as a baddie.

50.title: Wrestlemaniac
50.plot: In the SEASON FINALE, Brian discovers yet another crossover between pro wrestling and horror movies. Leyla Milani and the original Rey Misterio star in WRESTLEMANIAC.

imdb.title: Wrestling with Wregret
plot: Wrestling personality Brian Zane takes you on a journey through some of the strangest and stupidest things to ever occur in the world of professional wrestling.
